HEADWORD: Spindly
<hw>Spin"dly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Long and slender, or
disproportionately tall and slender; <as>as, <ex>spindly</ex>
legs.</as>. Used in some cases to suggest weakness.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> spindling.</syn>
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>spin doctor</ent>⟦br⟧
